\u201cFour Little Friends\u201d is all about celebrating innocence. It takes you on a journey to the world of Neetu, Mini, Rohan and Chintu the four little friends who always play together. Their playtimes are filled with little challenges which they overcome in their own innocent ways. Each story is exciting, hilarious and also heart-touching. Children in any part of the world can relate to these stories. As you go through the book you actually feel like being a part of the story and have fun with the four little friends. Prerana Wakade, a Mumbaikar at heart, settled in Bangalore, which is now her home, has donned many hats. A Banker, Writer, Poet, Artist, Singer, and above all a doting Mother of two wonderful twins. A graduate in English Literature from R. A. Ruia College, Mumbai, she spent 27 years working in the State Bank of India. She happily left her job to pursue her passion for writing stories. She enjoys weaving stories around her characters, touches them with a dash of humor, and lights up the moments in her stories. She writes proficiently in two languages, English and Marathi.
